15 SECTION 3. G.S. 136-189.11 reads as rewritten:
16 "§ 136-189.11. Transportation Investment Strategy Formula.
17 …
18 (b) Funds Excluded From Formula. – The following funds are not subject to this section:
19 (1) Federal congestion mitigation and air quality improvement program funds
20 appropriated to the State by the United States pursuant to 23 U.S.C. §
21 104(b)(2) and 23 U.S.C. § 149.
22 (1a) Federal Carbon Reduction Program formula funds appropriated to the State.
23 (2) Funds received through competitive awards or discretionary grants through
24 federal appropriations either for local governments, transportation authorities,
25 transit authorities, or the Department.
26 (3) Funds received from the federal government that under federal law may only
27 be used for Appalachian Development Highway System projects.
28 (4) Funds used in repayment of "GARVEE" bonds related to Phase I of the
29 Yadkin River Veterans Memorial Bridge project.
30 (5) Funds committed to gap funding for toll roads funded with bonds issued
31 pursuant to G.S. 136-176.
32 (6) Funds obligated for projects in the State Transportation Improvement
33 Program that are scheduled for construction as of October 1, 2013, in State
34 fiscal year 2012-2013, 2013-2014, or 2014-2015.
35 (7) Toll collections from a turnpike project under Article 6H of this Chapter and
36 other revenue from the sale of the Authority's bonds or notes or project loans,
37 in accordance with G.S. 136-89.192.
38 (8) Toll collections from the State-maintained ferry system collected under the
39 authority of G.S. 136-82.
40 (9) Federal State Planning and Research Program funds (23 U.S.C. § 505) and
41 Metropolitan Planning funds (23 U.S.C. §§ 104 and 134).
42 (10) Federal Lands Access Program funds received by the State pursuant to 23
43 U.S.C. § 204.
44 (11) Funds advanced pursuant to G.S. 136-186.
45 (12) Funds appropriated to the North Carolina State Ports Authority for the
46 purposes described in G.S. 136-176(b3).
47 (13) Federal Surface Transportation Program-Direct Attributable funds expended
48 on eligible projects.
49 (b1) Funds Excluded From Regional Impact Project Category. – Federal Surface
50 Transportation Program-Direct Attributable funds expended on eligible projects in the Regional
51 Impact Project category are excluded from that category.
