36 (4) Criteria for nonhighway projects. – Nonhighway projects subject to this
37 subsection shall be evaluated through a separate prioritization process
38 established by the Department that complies with all of the following:
39 a. The criteria used for selection of projects for a particular transportation
40 mode shall be based on a minimum of four quantitative criteria.
41 b. Local input shall include rankings of projects identified by the
42 Department's Transportation Division Engineers, Metropolitan
43 Planning Organizations, and Rural Transportation Planning
44 Organizations. Transportation Division Engineer local input scoring
45 shall take into account public comments. The Department shall ensure
46 that the public has a full opportunity to submit public comments, by
47 widely available notice to the public, an adequate time period for input,
48 and public hearings. Board of Transportation input shall be in
49 accordance with G.S. 136-189.11(g)(1) and G.S. 143B-350(g).
