27 (2) Funds obtained from local government funding participation. – Upon
28 authorization to construct a project with funds obtained by local government
29 funding participation, the Department shall make available for allocation as
30 set forth in subdivision (4) of this section an amount equal to one-half of the
31 local funding commitment for other eligible highway projects that serve the
32 local entity or entities that provided the local funding.
33 (3) Funds obtained through highway tolling. – Upon authorization to construct a
34 project with funding from toll revenue, the Department shall make available
35 for allocation an amount equal to one-half of the project construction cost
36 derived from toll revenue bonds. Upon authorization to construct a toll project
37 in which no project construction cost is derived from toll revenue bonds, the
38 Department shall make available for allocation an amount equal to one-half
39 of the revenue expected from the project over the first 10 years of the project,
40 less operations costs, as set forth in the Investment Grade Traffic and Revenue
41 Study. The amount made available for allocation to other eligible highway
42 projects shall not exceed two hundred million dollars ($200,000,000) of the
43 capital construction funding directly attributable to the highway toll revenues
44 committed in the Investment Grade Traffic and Revenue Study, for a project
45 for which funds have been committed on or before July 1, 2015. The amount
46 made available for allocation to other eligible highway projects shall not
47 exceed one hundred million dollars ($100,000,000) of the capital construction
48 funding directly attributable to the highway toll revenues committed in the
49 Investment Grade Traffic and Revenue Study, for a project for which funds
50 are committed after July 1, 2015. If the toll project is located in one or more
